column2: #Error: The tuning parameter grid should have columns nrounds, max_depth, eta, gamma, colsample_bytree, min_child_weight, subsample
param_grid <- expand.grid(
nrounds = c(100, 300),            # Number of boosting rounds
max_depth = c(2, 3,5),          # Maximum depth of a tree, used to control overfitting: 3-10 ; [1-∞]
gamma = c(0),                     # Minimum loss reduction: tuned depending on loss function; [0-∞]
colsample_bytree = c(1),          # Denotes the fraction of columns to be random samples for each tree: 0.5-1
min_child_weight = c(1),          # Minimum sum of instance weight (hessian): tuned using CV
subsample = c(1)                  # Denotes the fraction of observations ot be random samples for each tree: 0.5-1; [1-∞]
)                                   #also: max_leaf_nodes, max_delta_step, colsample_bylevel,lambda (ridge regression), alpha(Lasso), scale_pos_weight
# Display the structure to confirm multiple combinations
str(param_grid)

train_control <- trainControl(
method = "cv",              # Use cross-validation
number = 5,                 # 5-fold cross-validation
verboseIter = TRUE          # Print training progress
# Train the model with the updated parameter grid
model <- train(
x = X_baseline,
y = cbcl_scr_syn_internal_t_vector,
method = "xgbTree",
tuneGrid = param_grid,
trControl = train_control,
metric = "RMSE"
